ume, and a sample of your design work.nullnull','Graphic Design Intern for a Leading Web Design Company','','publish','closed','closed','','graphic-design-intern-for-a-leading-web-design-company','','','2018-04-17 07:53:29','2018-04-17 07:53:29','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1960',0,'noo_job','',0),(1961,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Lumina','Lumina','','publish','closed','closed','','lumina','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1962,30,'2018-02-05 00:00:00','2018-02-05 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nWho we are:\r\n\r\nMore Gardens! - Rooted in arts and education, we are artists, community people, community gardeners, and environmental and social justice activists. We promote the enhancement and preservation of community gardens as well as the cultivation of fallow land in New York City.\r\n\r\nMore Gardens! Project: Redesigning an existing 4-floor tenement building to be integrated into the adjoining community garden. Using majority passive design to create a diverse flourishing environment flowing from the building into the garden and vice-versa. As a whole embracing nature, culture, arts, and wellness.\r\n\r\nIntern Position, Unpaid:\r\n\r\nInspirational architectural drawings and plans that integrate an existing building with adjacent community green space in NYC.\r\n\r\nHere are some of our past sketches:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.moregardens.org/moregardenyc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">http://www.moregardens.org/moregardenyc/</a>\r\n\r\nWe are following the \"One Planet Living\" framework:\r\n\r\nHealth and happiness: Encouraging active, sociable, meaningful lives to promote good health and well being\r\n\r\nEquity and local economy: Creating bioregional economies that support equity\r\n\r\nCulture and community: Respecting and reviving local identity, wisdom, and culture; encouraging the involvement of people in shaping their community and creating a new culture of sustainability\r\n\r\nLand use and wildlife: Protecting and restoring biodiversity and creating new natural habitats through good land use and integration into the built environment\r\n\r\nSustainable water: Using water efficiently in buildings, farming, and manufacturing. Designing to avoid local issues such as flooding, drought and watercourse pollution\r\n\r\nLocal and sustainable food: Supporting sustainable and humane farming, promoting access to healthy, low impact, local, seasonal and organic diets and reducing food waste\r\n\r\nSustainable materials: Using sustainable and healthy products, such as those with low embodied energy, sourced locally, made from renewable or waste resources\r\n\r\nSustainable transport: Reducing the need to travel, and encouraging low and zero carbon modes of transport to reduce emissions\r\n\r\nZero waste: Reducing waste, reusing where possible, and ultimately sending zero waste to landfill\r\n\r\nZero carbon: Making buildings energy efficient and delivering all energy with renewable technologies\r\n\r\nIntern Position:\r\n\r\nCreating inspirational architectural drawings and plans following above framework\r\n\r\nCollaborating in participatory design with staff and community garden members in NYC.\r\n\r\nIntegrating Biomorphic, Organic, Permaculture, Sacred Geometry and Feng Shui principles.\r\n\r\nUtilizing hand drawings as well as AutoCAD and SketchUp\r\n\r\nLocation: We would like face to face collaboration in NYC, we are also open to working remotely.\r\n\r\nWhen: Rolling basis. Start date May 30, 2018\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\nUtilizing hand drawings as well as AutoCAD and SketchUp\r\n\r\nParticipatory design alongside community members\r\n\r\nWorking with staff to draw out large-scale overall vision plan\r\n\r\nDetailed sketches and drawings of buildings as well as growing areas, playgrounds\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\nWe receive a lot of applications and we highly recommend a paragraph to explain why you have chosen the More Gardens program, in the \"Personal Message from Applicant\" box, unless already in the resume, please add links of your work that matches our internship application.\r\n\r\nGraduate level or Senior/Junior Architectural Students\r\n\r\nCreating inspirational architectural drawings and plans following above framework\r\n\r\nCollaborating in participatory design with staff and community garden members in NYC.\r\n\r\nIntegrating Biomorphic, Organic, Permaculture, Sacred Geometry and Feng Shui principles.','Design of Super Green Building integrated with a community garden in NYC','','publish','closed','closed','','design-of-super-green-building-integrated-with-a-community-garden-in-nyc','','','2018-04-17 07:53:55','2018-04-17 07:53:55','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1962',0,'noo_job','',0),(1963,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','More Gardens! Fund','More Gardens! Fund','','publish','closed','closed','','more-gardens-fund','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1964,30,'2017-11-06 00:00:00','2017-11-06 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nThe members of Legacy Financial Group have been providing personalized planning for individuals and business\' in Northern Colorado for the past decade. As a financial representative intern for Legacy, youll get real-world job experience as you discover a career with flexibility and rewards. You will work with our team in our Old Town Fort Collins office. We will help you master our personalized planning process to provide financial solutions tailored to each clients needs over his or her lifetime. Legacy Financial Group has teamed with financial services industry leader, New York Life, to provide a formalized training platform. New York Life is number 61 on the Fortune 500 list and is one of the top mutual insurance companies in the industry. This training will help you build on your classroom learning and develop lifelong skills.