understanding of the English language as well as the digital media landscape, including various social media websites. Candidates will need to be able to do proofreading as well as copy editing . Company is currently redesigning our website, and will soon launch a social media campaign. The intern hired for this position will need strong critical thinking skills in order to integrate into our vibrant and passionate team who are very excited to share this exciting launch with an intern hoping to gain a ton of great online experience. Writing and editing skills are required. \n<br />Responsibilities \n<br /> Contribute to editorial team \n<br /> Monitor and post on blogs, forums, and social networks \n<br /> Online outreach and promotion using Facebook, Instagram LinkedIn, Twitter, and more \n<br /> Website and social media optimization \n<br /> Keyword analysis \n<br /> Cost/benefit analysis \n<br /> \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> Research, reading manuscripts, writing press releases and working with authors.<h2>Requirements</h2> Requirements \n<br />Students applying for this internship should be Marketing/Business or Language majors, with 3 years of experience on the Web and a solid understanding of youth markets. \n<br />Majors \n<br />Marketing, Business, Communications, English','Editorial and Social Media Associate','','publish','closed','closed','','editorial-and-social-media-associate','','','2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1974',0,'noo_job','',0),(1975,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Mango Media','Mango Media','','publish','closed','closed','','mango-media','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1977,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> The Institute \n<br />Seven Pillars Institute (SPI) for Global Finance and Ethics (\n<a href=\"https://sevenpillarsinstitute.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://sevenpillarsinstitute.org</a>) is the worlds only independent think-tank for research, education and promotion of financial ethics. \n<br /> \n<br />SPI is a, nonprofit, nonpartisan, organization whose mission is to highlight and analyze issues of moral philosophy in global financial markets with a view to enhancing ethical practice and policy. At its highest level of aspiration the Institute aims to develop a new theory of finance that incorporates ethics at a fundamental level. SPI is at the forefront of efforts to shape the emergent, crucial and practical field of financial ethics. \n<br /> \n<br />SPI is affiliated with the University of London (Queen Mary College) and its Fellows and Interns work from around the globe. The Prospect Think Tank Awards 2016 shortlisted and cited the research of SPI on climate change mitigation, praising its deft work on eco-tourism. The Awards are an annual recognition of the influential work carried out by think tanks across the globe. \n<br /> \n<br />The Internship \n<br />Established in 2010, SPI is building on its early accomplishments. Therefore, SPI is recruiting interns who are looking for opportunities to contribute and help develop an exciting, green field venture that endeavors to make the world a better place. The internship will provide invaluable experience in research, writing, entrepreneurship, and organizational development. In addition, each intern will be listed and featured on the website of the Institute. Research and writing projects will be attributed to their authors. Consequently, the internship is a unique and rare opportunity for students to publish scholarly work. \n<br /> \n<br />These published works reach a global audience. As a result of this exposure, former interns have been invited to speak at international conferences and to have their articles republished in well-regarded academic journals. In addition, RealClearMarkets, a widely read financial news website, has frequently cited essays published on the SPI website. \n<br /> \n<br />At the end of the internship period, the Institute will award three prizes for the best essays or research submitted by an intern. The prize comprises a cash award of US$250 each. \n<br /> \n<br />The Institute does not require interns to reside in Kansas City, Missouri during the term of the internship. Individual work may be performed offsite while meetings and collaborative work will be done online. \n<br /><h3>Responsibilities</h3> Interns are required to do research and writing on issues related to finance and ethics. During the term of the internship, research associates are expected to produce and submit at least two research projects in the form of written papers (videos, slides or power point presentations also are acceptable). Articles should be well-written, researched and be of publishable quality. Interns will be given topics on which to write or research but self-designed topics are allowed if appropriate. Interns will be given editorial comments on their research and guidance on improving their projects. Research and writing projects will be attributed to their authors. The internship is a unique and rare opportunity for students to publish scholarly work.<h2>Requirements</h2> The Internship \n<br />Established in 2010, SPI is building on its early accomplishments. Therefore, SPI is recruiting interns who are looking for opportunities to contribute and help develop an exciting, green field venture that endeavors to make the world a better place. The internship will provide invaluable experience in research, writing, entrepreneurship, and organizational development. In addition, each intern will be listed and featured on the website of the Institute. Research and writing projects will be attributed to their authors. Consequently, the internship is a unique and rare opportunity for students to publish scholarly work. \n<br /> \n<br />These published works reach a global audience. As a result of this exposure, former interns have been invited to speak at international conferences and to have their articles republished in well-regarded academic journals. In addition, RealClearMarkets, a widely read financial news website, has frequently cited essays published on the SPI website. \n<br /> \n<br />Qualifications \n<br /> \n<br />Ideal candidates will be undergraduate students majoring in Philosophy, Finance, Business, Economics, Public Policy, Politics, History, Law or Journalism or graduate students pursuing a master or doctoral degree in these fields. The candidate should have strong writing, research, and inter-personal skills, and be eager to take the initiative. In addition, he or she should preferably be self-driven, at ease with online collaboration and effectively use social media. \n<br /> \n<br />The Institute does not require interns to reside in Kansas City, Missouri during the term of the internship. Individual work may be performed offsite while meetings and collaborative work will be done online. \n<br /> \n<br />Apart from the essay/research prize, internships are unpaid. Students may apply for credit from their department or school. Successful interns not only will be able to publish their work, but also will obtain a strong letter of recommendation.','Summer Research Associate','','publish','closed','closed','','summer-research-associate','','','2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1977',0,'noo_job','',0),(1978,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Seven Pillars Institute for Global Fiinance and Ethics','Seven Pillars Institute for Global Fiinance and Ethics','','publish','closed','closed','','seven-pillars-institute-for-global-fiinance-and-ethics','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1979,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nThe internship program prepares students to obtain leadership roles on future political campaigns Our 30+ day program is both intensive and comprehensive by assigning interns to essential roles within the senior staff of a campaign. Our program focuses on main competencies including direct voter contact, electoral/organizational systems training, campaign business/operations/finance training, and becoming a diverse field director. Many of our previous interns have graduated from our program and get promoted to a management role on a campaign generally during the become a manager for a campaign during an immediately following cycle.\r\n\r\nDirect Voter Contact:\r\n\r\nOnce a campaign plan has been set into a strategic ground game plan, the main goal of the campaign (despite the differences amongst our clients/candidates) and their respective districts) is to target a specific audience of voters. By selecting a specific audience you continuously increase the effectiveness of your campaign by narrowing the amount of Voters we engage with while matching up the voter to our projected win number voters. Our grassroots approach to campaigns has multiple aspects to it including identifying voter support, increasing voter turnout, and conducting polls. Identifying voter support can take two main forms that are door to door canvassing and phone banking. We will train interns to maximize contact efforts through direct interaction and train them in a way to manipulate a conversation to lead up to a hard ask, which is a very direct and clear question addressed to voters. This information allows a campaign to target specific voters and communities to increase support for a candidate and boost turnout.\r\n\r\nSystems Training:\r\n\r\nAll political campaigns have various systems of data management and use different systems to control and analyze data. Interns will be trained to manage data including information obtained through direct voter contact and will learn how to critically analyze this data as to formulate campaign strategy. Managing and analyzing this data will entail use of various software including excel and VAN.\r\n\r\nLeadership:\r\n\r\nOne of the most important competencies to run an effective campaign. Our internship program offers a unique opportunity for interns to try out various methods to improve a campaigns efficiency at persuading voters to support a candidate. By learning how to formulate effective persuasive conversations, interns will be prepared to be leaders and take initiatives themselves.nullnull','Campaign Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','campaign-intern','','','2018-04-15 14:50:47','2018-04-15 14:50:47','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1979',0,'noo_job','',0),(1980,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','North Shore Strategies','North Shore Strategies','','publish','closed','closed','','north-shore-strategies','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1981,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nThis is an unpaid internship, college credit is available. Must be available at least 3 days a week and a minimum of 4 hours a day.\r\n\r\nNALIP (The National Association of Latino Independent Producers) is seeking to fill an Event Planning intern position! We are looking for a motivated, detail-oriented, organized, go-getter to help us plan and execute our upcoming events. We plan workshops, panels and a four day conference that includes screenings and an awards gala. This role offers a great hands-on experience with an established non-profit organization.\r\n\r\nNALIP is a non-profit that serves to promote, advance, inspire and advocate for Latinx and diverse content creators across media.\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\nProvide extensive administrative support that includes research.\r\n\r\nAssist in event set-up, tear down, and execution of events.\r\n\r\nWork with Events &amp; Communications coordinators on marketing and events promotion.\r\n\r\nManage event ticketing check-in and RSVP/guest lists.\r\n\r\nBuild and cultivate relationships with potential outreach partners.\r\n\r\nCreate a welcoming and warm environment at events with superb customer service.\r\n\r\nAct as strategic thought partner in event strategies and implementations.\r\n\r\nWrite a comprehensive written wrap report as directed.\r\n\r\nBe open to doing other smaller tasks that are not in your department.\r\n\r\nMake your colleagues laugh or half-smile.\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\nBachelors Degree or currently enrolled in undergraduate studies.\r\n\r\nMust be able to come into the office a minimum of 2-3 days.\r\n\r\nMust be well organized, flexible and able to work under pressure.\r\n\r\nSelf starter who takes initiative with enthusiasm in creating their work.\r\n\r\nMust be energetic and very proactive, someone who welcomes a challenge and is able to work in a fast-moving, demanding, flexible environment with limited day-to-day supervision.\r\n\r\nAdept at managing several projects and coordinating with multiple stakeholders.\r\n\r\nAbility to handle high volume of complex projects and tasks for multiple people and departments simultaneously and manage competing priorities.\r\n\r\nDeadline-oriented with strong time management skills.\r\n\r\nMust possess excellent verbal and written communication skills to communicate effectively with internal and external teams.\r\n\r\nAccuracy, productivity and dependability are important attributes.\r\n\r\nAble to work event hours. Your shifts will shift based on event schedules, and you must be able to work evenings and/or weekends based on our event calendar.\r\n\r\nMust have dependable transportation for events and other job related activities.','Event Planning Internship','','publish','closed','closed','','event-planning-internship','','','2018-04-15 14:51:39','2018-04-15 14:51:39','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1981',0,'noo_job','',0),(1982,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','NALIP (National Association of Independent Producers)','NALIP (National Association of Independent Producers)','','publish','closed','closed','','nalip-national-association-of-independent-producers','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1983,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nThis is an unpaid internship, college credit is available. Must be available at least 3 days a week and a minimum of 4 hours a day.\r\n\r\nThe National Association of Latino Independent Producers (NALIP) is seeking motivated, hard-working individuals to join the Digital Production Team. As the premiere non-profit organization working to promote and advocate for Latinos in media, we are constantly producing content to move careers forward. The Digital Production Team oversees all original content produced by NALIP in addition to the development and preparation for the NALIP Media Summit.\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\nCapture BTS footage and still photography of NALIP Productions.\r\n\r\nCreate highlight/sizzle reels from archived footage.\r\n\r\nBrainstorm and develop various forms of promotional material.\r\n\r\nOrganize and maintain multiple hard drives.\r\n\r\nResearch upcoming trends and Latino content creators.\r\n\r\nResearch potential partnerships/collaborations for the NALIP Media Summit.\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\nBe proficient in DSLR workflows.\r\n\r\nBe proficient in Adobe Suite or Creative Cloud  Premiere Pro (Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects and Final Cut are a plus).\r\n\r\nHave working knowledge of codecs, frame rates and delivery formats.\r\n\r\nWork well within a team.\r\n\r\nBe able to both provide and respond well to constructive criticism.\r\n\r\nPay high attention to detail.\r\n\r\nHave prior experience managing multiple, simultaneous projects.','Digital Production Internship','','publish','closed','closed','','digital-production-internship','','','2018-04-15 14:52:17','2018-04-15 14:52:17','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1983',0,'noo_job','',0),(1984,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nThis is an unpaid internship; college credit is available. Must be available at least 3 days a week and a minimum of 4 hours a day.\r\n\r\nThe National Association of Latino Independent Producers (NALIP) is seeking creative, motivated and hard-working Graphic Designers to join the Digital Production Department as part of the Graphic Design Team. As the premiere non-profit organization working to promote and advocate for Latinos in media, we are constantly producing content to move careers forward in front and behind the camera. The Graphic Design Team is the driving force behind designing the overall look of Programs, Events and\r\n\r\nCampaigns for NALIP. Working with the Digital Production Team we provide graphic assets for original content and work alongside the Communications Team with Websites and Social Media.\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\n Collaborate with other Designers.\r\n\r\n Brainstorm/Design assets for our Sites, Social Networks and other departments as needed.\r\n\r\n Photo editing, gathering and researching.\r\n\r\n Work with news outlets, studios and sponsors with their materials and providing graphics.\r\n\r\n Create digital materials to be printed (Booklets, Shirts, Signage, Step &amp; Repeats, Banners.)\r\n\r\n Research upcoming trends and Latino content creators.\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\n Showcase a strong sense of Design and Typography skills.\r\n\r\n Be proficient in Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign.)\r\n\r\n Work well within a team.\r\n\r\n Can both provide and respond well to constructive criticism.\r\n\r\n Attention to the details.\r\n\r\n Manage multiple projects and prioritize tasks.\r\n\r\n Drawing/Illustration skills a plus.\r\n\r\n Familiarity with editing and motion graphics software a plus.\r\n\r\n All applicants MUST send a link to a portfolio or website with samples of work.','Graphic Design Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','graphic-design-intern-2','','','2018-04-16 02:16:23','2018-04-16 02:16:23','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1984',0,'noo_job','',0),(1985,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nNALIPs Communications department is looking for a dedicated intern that will help in building and maintaining its robust communication platform through a variety of content and media platforms related to NALIPs mission, programs and events. In addition to these communication assignments, the intern will be introduced to the major topics and issues related to arts advocacy, nonprofit management, community organizing, and communication best practices.\r\n\r\nThis is an unpaid internship, college credit is available. Must be available at least 3 days a week and a minimum of 4 hours a day.\r\n\r\nApart with from learning basic administrative practices (phone/email etiquette, project organization skills, sponsor/media and membership relations, and basic office management), in supporting NALIPs communications department, intern will learn how to create and execute a communications strategy that is program and events based, while adhering to our organization\'s mission and branding. As a NALIP team member, intern will close program understanding how to be a team player in a professional media arts environment.\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\nResearch Latino Entertainment topics.\r\n\r\nAssist in maintaining NALIP social media and website.\r\n\r\nAssist in newsletter curation and articles.\r\n\r\nWrite blog posts on NALIP news and events.\r\n\r\nAssist in program events from their planning, production, and post.\r\n\r\nAssist with ongoing administrative tasks, database management, membership correspondence and participate in staff meetings.\r\n\r\nServe as NALIP representative attending outside events with partner organizations and companies.\r\n\r\nWork with public relations team in writing press releases, talent invitations, and talent management.\r\n\r\nPut together and keep track cross promotional agreements with partnerships.\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\nIdeal candidates will identify with our mission and have a deep interest in media arts, entertainment, and communication.\r\n\r\nExcellent writing, communication, and research skills are required.\r\n\r\nProficient with Google apps (docs, sheets, etc.), social media, and computer programs such as Microsoft and Excel.\r\n\r\nBilingual applicants are encouraged.\r\n\r\nBe able to work in a fast-pace environment with time-sensitive deadlines.\r\n\r\nWilling to learn and be coached.\r\n\r\nApplicants with graphic design or video production experience are encouraged.\r\n\r\nPublicity experience is a plus.','Communications and Publicity Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','communications-and-publicity-intern','','','2018-04-15 13:29:29','2018-04-15 13:29:29','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1985',0,'noo_job','',0),(1986,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nWe are in the process of building an online community based on exposing, discussing and evaluating alternative news streams and information called Yebo (THEYEBO.COM).\r\n\r\nQualities essential for working with YEBO are:\r\n\r\nan open mind\r\n\r\ncognitive thinking skills\r\n\r\na need to know\r\n\r\na desire to grow\r\n\r\na sense that something is not right in this world\r\n\r\nthe need to set things right, to help the planet in a large way, to expose truth and obtain true social progress\r\n\r\nYour education is not as important to us as your life skills and areas of private study and passion.This is a growth position. We are interested in those with a burning desire to create positive change in this world.\r\n\r\nWe are non-sectarian humanists. We do not delineate ourselves as \"liberal,\" \"conservative,\" Christian, Hindu, trans, gay, straight, Black, White, \"democratic\" or \"republican.\" We seek to unite, not divide through labelling or accusations. We are humans sharing this planet, first and foremost.\r\n\r\nIf you \"hate\" Trump, or anyone else, do NOT apply. We want open, vibrant minds willing to question established belief systems and get to the bottom of things.\r\n\r\nIf this seems like a lot of information for interns, then you are right. But we believe in the long view, and are looking for the right people to join our venture as partners, not employees.\r\n\r\nNecessary skills for this position:\r\n\r\nexcellent speaking skills as you will be speaking and interviewing on camera\r\n\r\nwriting ability\r\n\r\ninterest in true journalism\r\n\r\nquick thinking\r\n\r\nknowledge of social media marketing\r\n\r\nfilmmaking and editing ability\r\n\r\nwordpress ability a plus\r\n\r\nsense of humor or irony\r\n\r\nThe job:\r\n\r\nCreate short videos on the topics provided 1-3 minutes in length, edit as necessary, post to YEBO video sites, provide description, post to social media and Yebo blog.\r\n\r\nEach completed video will receive $10. The amount you produce is up to you, however we respond to quality not quantity.\r\n\r\nHOW TO APPLY FOR THIS JOB\r\n\r\nSend a short video no longer than 1 minute in length describing as much as possible of the following:\r\n\r\nwho you are\r\n\r\nyour beliefs\r\n\r\nyour skills\r\n\r\nyour passions\r\n\r\nwhat you would like to accomplish in this position\r\n\r\nONLY VIDEO RESPONSES WILL BE CONSIDERED. Include a 1 to 2 sentences cover letter as to why you are responding. In other words, what has resonated with you?\r\n\r\nYou may include relevant experience in the body of your email. Document attachments will not be read.\r\n\r\nWe greatly look forward to hearing from you.\r\n\r\nJob Type: Internship\r\n\r\nSalary: $10.00 /posted video\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\nCreate short videos on the topics provided 1-3 minutes in length, edit as necessary, post to YEBO video sites, provide description, post to social media and Yebo blog.\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\nYour education is not as important to us as your life skills and areas of private study and passion.This is a growth position. We are interested in those with open minds and a deep desire to create positive change in this world.','Video/Film Interns','','publish','closed','closed','','videofilm-interns','','','2018-04-15 13:33:32','2018-04-15 13:33:32','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1986',0,'noo_job','',0),(1987,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Brooklyn Indie Press','Brooklyn Indie Press','','publish','closed','closed','','brooklyn-indie-press','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(1988,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nAzoland Pictures is a Los Angeles based film distribution company that specializes on Japanese feature films and anime films. We also plan and organize film festivals and Japanese related events.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for interns who are highly motivated and passionate about gaining experience in the industry.\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\n- Create newsletters, online promotions, etc.\r\n\r\n- Assist the staff prepare and operate the company\'s events.\r\n\r\n- Provide support to social media efforts to target new audiences.\r\n\r\n- Research and analyze marketing and sales materials.\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\n- Proficient written and verbal communication skills in English.\r\n\r\n- Familiar with social network sites (Facebook, twitter, instagram, etc)\r\n\r\n- Microsoft Office (word, excel, powerpoint)\r\n\r\n- Understand Japanese culture and at least have beginner level of Japanese language skills','Marketing Intern','','publish','closed','closed','','marketing-intern-2','','','2018-04-15 13:44:11','2018-04-15 13:44:11','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=1988',0,'noo_job','',0),(1989,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','