d Holidays\r\n\r\n Vacation/Personal after 1 yearnull\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\nJob Requirements:\r\n\r\n Must be dependable, responsible, have initiative and able to work\r\n\r\nwithout someone looking over your shoulder\r\n\r\n Superior customer service skills\r\n\r\n Experience handling money required\r\n\r\n Computer skills\r\n\r\n Collection experience a plus\r\n\r\n Valid driver\'s license and acceptable driving record\r\n\r\n Ability to pass a criminal background check\r\n\r\n Must submit to drug screening','Administrative Aides','','publish','closed','closed','','administrative-aides','','','2018-04-17 06:10:59','2018-04-17 06:10:59','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2063',0,'noo_job','',0),(2064,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nLeft Forum seeks volunteers to work alongside our experienced organizers and other volunteers in engaging our extensive list of speakers for our annual Left Forum Conference (to be held June 1st - 3rd, 2018).\r\n\r\nABOUT LEFT FORUM\r\n\r\nContinuing a tradition that began in the 1960s, Left Forum convenes an international conference each year in New York City. The conference involves a broad spectrum of progressive intellectuals, organizers, and academics, who come together to share ideas to transform the world; to better understand commonalities, differences, and alternatives to current predicaments; and to engage a wide range of critical perspectives on the world. Left Forum 2017 drew approximately 4,000 participants for 400 panels.\r\n\r\nABOUT THIS VOLUNTEER POSITION\r\n\r\nEvery year, Left Forum staff, volunteers, and interns work to engage progressive, left, academic, and activist communities for our annual conference. One of the most important aspects of this work is outreach to past and potential speakers and panelists. The goal of this work is to encourage these people to join us once again as speakers by submitting a panel proposal. Specific task-examples include phone and email outreach, correspondence with speakers leading up to the conference, outreach strategy collaboration, and more.\r\n\r\nThe ideal person for this role is someone who is committed to social justice, self-motivated, comfortable taking on project-coordination and engaging in outreach via phone and email, a keen eye for detail, and the ability to bring creative ideas into organizational and administrative processes. Experience in administrative systems is also a plus.\r\n\r\nINTERESTED?\r\n\r\nIf you would like to talk to us about this volunteer opportunity and how it can be tailored to your interest and schedule, please feel free to reach out to us at: volunteer@leftforum.org\r\n\r\nnullnull','Outreach and Admin Projects Internship and Volunteer','','publish','closed','closed','','outreach-and-admin-projects-internship-and-volunteer','','','2018-04-17 06:11:16','2018-04-17 06:11:16','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2064',0,'noo_job','',0),(2065,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Left Forum','Left Forum','','publish','closed','closed','','left-forum','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(2066,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nJetzy is seeking multiple highly motivated and dedicated Videographer Trainees. The Videographer Trainees will be responsible for creating inspiring promotional videos of Jetzy community members. The Jetzy community consists of individuals who have a passion for life and experiences such as, travel, hiking, sports, culture, and food just to name a few. These videos will be posted on our social media to promote Jetzy as well as promote the Videographer Trainees work to gain exposure to our followers of over half a million.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\n-Interview Jezty community members about their passions and experiences\r\n\r\n- Make videos for things that you are passionate about ( i.e. trav