ch days activities.\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\nDuties\r\n\r\n Participate in orientation and training for the youth program\r\n\r\n Assist youth staff with planning and promoting summer programming during the month of June\r\n\r\n Implement and lead summer programming in July and August\r\n\r\n Participate in all program meetings and staff development activities\r\n\r\n Provide daily documentation/case notes for program participants\r\n\r\n Lead a small group of students through each days activities\r\n\r\n Aid in the distribution &amp; clean-up of materials and snacks\r\n\r\n Assist with transporting students to and from the program site and lead youth on field trips\r\n\r\n Act as a positive role model for refugee youth\r\n\r\n Assist staff with post-program evaluations and feedback and provide general support to the youth program staff\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\nKnowledge, Skills, and Abilities\r\n\r\n Support of World Reliefs mission, vision and values statement\r\n\r\n Ability to work well with people of other cultural backgrounds\r\n\r\n Must demonstrate energy and flexibility\r\n\r\n Ability to handle chaos and work well under pressure\r\n\r\n Ability to start and work on projects independently and follow through to completion\r\n\r\n Competent in the use of Microsoft Office\r\n\r\n Ability to communicate clearly, both orally and in writing\r\n\r\n Flexible and motivated team player\r\n\r\nExperience Required\r\n\r\n Proven experience and ability to relate well to children and adolescents\r\n\r\n Experience working with youth or adults from other cultures domestically or overseas a plus\r\n\r\nPhysical Demands\r\n\r\n Ability to lift 25 pounds\r\n\r\nWork Environment\r\n\r\n Office located in Chicago, IL\r\n\r\n Various modes of public transportation available\r\n\r\n Workspace may be shared with existing staff','Youth Summer Learning Program Internship','','publish','closed','closed','','youth-summer-learning-program-internship','','','2018-04-17 06:55