 encourage participation \n<br /> Assist with event planning in areas such as logistics, promotion, volunteer recruitment, registration tracking, etc. \n<br /> Provide assistance with preparing and distributing event materials \n<br /><h2>Requirements</h2> Qualifications \n<br /> Knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite, Google Docs, and comfortable with database work \n<br /> Experience using Raisers Edge a plus, but not required \n<br /> Flexibility and willingness to step in and provide hands-on assistance as needed \n<br /> Ability to handle many projects and manage tasks independently \n<br /> Outgoing, energetic personality \n<br /> Interest in special events and fundraising a plus \n<br />','Event Planning & Promotion Internship: The Longest Day, RIDE To End Alzheimers, Run to End Alzheime','','publish','closed','closed','','event-planningpromotion-internship-the-longest-day-ride-to-end-alzheimers-run-to-end-alzheime','','','2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2188',0,'noo_job','',0),(2189,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> A Real-World Experience with Real-World Impact! \n<br />The American Red Cross prevents and alleviates human suffering in the face of emergencies by mobilizing the power of volunteers and the generosity of donors. \n<br /> \n<br />American Red Cross Greater New York interns are involved in projects critical to the day-to-day work of our non-profit organization, gaining an insiders perspective on the Red Cross humanitarian mission as well as service delivery at the local and national levels. In our region, you will enjoy a collaborative work culture committed to the diversity of our people, programs, and services. \n<br /> \n<br />Mission Concept: &quot;Communicate Our Mission&quot; \n<br />This mission concept is for students who are strong public speakers, good writers, and savvy about social media. You want to be part of communicating the Red Cross mission-- behind-the-scenes, on-camera, in-person and online through media. \n<br /> \n<br />This mission concept is for students who are reliable and very detail-oriented. You want to work behind-the-scenes using your administrative superpowers to help the Red Cross stay organized and keep its services running smoothly and efficiently. \n<br /> \n<br />What Youll Learn \n<br /> Leadership \n<br /> Teamwork \n<br /> Relationship Building \n<br /> Organizational Management \n<br /> Training and mentoring from subject matter experts \n<br /> Volunteer Engagement, Management &amp; Administration \n<br /> A deeper awareness of the Humanitarian Mission of the American Red Cross \n<br /> Cultivation of Cultural Competence and Inclusion<h3>Responsibilities</h3> Internship Opportunities \n<br /> \n<br />Intern, Communications - Media Relations, NYC \n<br /> What You\'ll Do: In this position, youll learn how to develop communications and media relations strategies and be exposed to various facets of communications including social media, public relations, media relations, video, and photography. You will also interview volunteers, partners, and recipients of Red Cross services for blog stories and develop, write, edit and proof communications materials such as press releases, web stories, blog posts and event scripts. Special Skills: Strong writing skills, with experience writing, formatting, and posting clear content. Youll be asked to submit writing samples. \n<br /> \n<br />Intern, Communications - Marketing, NYC \n<br /> What Youll Do: You will support the Marketing &amp; Communications Department to effectively use marketing intelligence to better communicate with our supporters, raise more money, help more people in a disaster, solicit more blood donations, and more. Interns will learn how to create, monitor, and curate interesting and effective content for social media platforms. Interns will learn from subject matter experts the policies and procedures in working with social media in a professional collaborative environment. Special Skills: Marketing statistics, data targeting, experience with HTML or any data programming language is preferred but not required. Familiarity with Web Analytics and data interpretation preferred. \n<br /> \n<br />Intern, Communications - Social Media, NYC \n<br /> What Youll Do: You will learn how to create, monitor, and curate interesting and effective content for social media platforms. Interns will also produce digital content (posts, photographs/captions, videos) to promote and raise awareness of Red Cross values, content, and activities on social media. Special Skills: Strong writing skills, with experience writing, formatting, and posting clear content  intern will be asked to submit writing samples, intermediate to advanced proficiency with Photoshop, iMovie, and Final Cut Pro X preferred, strong Photography/Videography skills preferred. \n<br /> \n<br />Intern, External Affairs, NYC \n<br /> What Youll Do: Support the team that manages relationships with our organizations external stakeholders so that they may advance our mission, inform people, inspire action and protect our brand and reputation. You will work on developing a communications plan based on industry best practices. Interns will conduct research, create a matrix, write talking points based on Red Cross guidelines, create possible public facing collateral materials. Your tasks may also include developing a communications plan based on industry best practices and writing talking points based on Red Cross guidelines.<h2>Requirements</h2> Eligibility \n<br />You must be enrolled in an undergraduate or graduate degree program at the time of the internship. Our Internship Program may not satisfy requirements for school practicums but can be done for credit. \n<br /> \n<br />Duration \n<br />Our formal Summer Internship Program typically runs for a specified 10-week duration. \n<br /> Monday, June 4th until Friday, August 10th \n<br /> Weekly Internship Hours Required: At least 24 hours per week \n<br /> \n<br />The intern selection process is highly competitive. Intern Managers make their final hiring decision on Wednesday, May 16th. \n<br /> \n<br />Preferred Majors \n<br />Communications, Journalism, Public Relations, Social Media \n<br /> \n<br />Preferred Grade Levels \n<br />Undergraduate Junior, Undergraduate Senior and Graduate level. \n<br /> \n<br />Our Ideal Candidate \n<br />Our ideal candidate is a mission-focused undergraduate or graduate college student seeking a meaningful internship experience who has the following qualities: \n<br /> Upbeat \n<br /> Detail Oriented \n<br /> Multi-Tasker \n<br /> Strong Communicator \n<br /> Team Builder/Player \n<br /> Self-Starter \n<br /> Client-Focused \n<br /> Strategic Thinker \n<br /> No-task-is too-small attitude','Unpaid Internship - Communicate Our Mission, Summer 2018','','publish','closed','closed','','unpaid-internship-communicate-our-mission-summer-2018','','','2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2189',0,'noo_job','',0),(2190,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','American Red Cross Greater New York','American Red Cross Greater New York','','publish','closed','closed','','american-red-cross-greater-new-york','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(2191,30,'2018-04-12 00:00:00','2018-04-12 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2> Jetzy is the world\'s first social platform to connect, empower and reward explorers &amp; curators of unique &amp; authentic local experiences. Whether it\'s travel, food, culture or outdoor adventures, on Jetzy you can contact like-minded people for friendships or off-beaten authentic recommendations, so you\'re never lost or alone anywhere you are. \n<br /> \n<br />Jetzy is a global social community from 350 cities but what we are really promoting is a lifestyle, an attitude of borderless citi