ies</h3>\r\n- Assist in all aspects of video and photographic communications and contribute to planning and storyboarding\r\n\r\n- Assist in the end-to-end process from storyboarding to logistics to shooting to editing and publishing\r\n\r\n- Film video and shoot photographs in studio and field environments\r\n\r\n- Record desktop computer screens and actions for demo and training videos\r\n\r\n- Use existing original and stock footage to produce new videos\r\n\r\n- Contribute to mixing and editing to create polished and engaging videos\r\n\r\n- Publish videos primarily to the web and touch-up still photography\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\n- Have the potential to deliver videos and photos that succinctly and clearly tell the desired story\r\n\r\n- Ability to deliver videos with cuts, graphics, sound and other elements that convey a quality production value and a level of technical sophistication\r\n\r\n- Experience with Final Cut Pro, Adobe Premiere, Adobe Captivate and Adobe Photoshop\r\n\r\n- Knowledge of digital videography and photography cameras and equipment\r\n\r\n-Reliable transportation for both city AND suburban work\r\n\r\n-Have a DSLR or Mirrorless camera (or consistent access to one)\r\n\r\n-Video editing experience\r\n\r\n-Provide examples of your previous work\r\n\r\n-Available for a video-shoot on a few days notice\r\n\r\n-Interest in commercial video work','Media Intern (Film/Video/Photo)','','publish','closed','closed','','media-intern-filmvideophoto-3','','','2018-04-17 07:41:10','2018-04-17 07:41:10','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2320',0,'noo_job','',0),(2321,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','Ruben Digital Media','Ruben Digital Media','','publish','closed','closed','','ruben-digital-media','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(2322,30,'2018-04-11 00:00:00','2018-04-11 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nABOUT MULTIVISIONNAIRE PICTURES\r\n\r\n=================================\r\n\r\nCompany: MultiVisionnaire Pictures is an established international film distribution and production company known in the global film industry. We are based in east side of Los Angeles, distribute and manage the marketing and financial processes for independent films worldwide. (\r\n<a href=\"http://www.multivisionnaire.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">www.multivisionnaire.com</a>)\r\n\r\nDESCRIPTION:\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a resourceful, dynamic self-starter to mentor. Non-paid intern will be mentored in the acquisition, distribution and marketing process of independent films and TV programs; and participate in the preparation of various international film markets (Cannes, American Film Market, etc.). The right candidate will gain invaluable, hands-on experience in the international film business.\r\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\r\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\r\n\r\n Assist with preparation for worldwide film markets with the team\r\n\r\n Assist with research, analysis and review of independent films\r\n\r\n Assist with marketing campaigns, screenings, film releases and film festivals\r\n\r\n Assist with international and domestic film distribution and delivery process\r\n\r\n Assist with company\'s PR and social media management\r\n\r\n Participate in development, research and production process of feature films and TV series\r\n\r\n Additional tasks and ad hoc projects to be determined\r\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\r\nQUALIFICATIONS :\r\n\r\n College major in film, media, marketing, communications, or related field with strong research skills\r\n\r\n Passion for films and high literacy in film elements and various genres of independent films\r\n\r\n Articulating and charismatic interpersonal communication in writing, in person and on the phone\r\n\r\n Personable, professional demeanor, ethical and able to handle confidential matters\r\n\r\n Attention to detail (prequalifier: read this listing closely and write a professional cover letter)\r\n\r\n Common sense and some basic software skills (Word, Excel, etc.)\r\n\r\n One of the following:\r\n\r\na) Script writing and reading experience\r\n\r\nb) Final Cut Pro editing skill and usage of HD video camera\r\n\r\nAPPLICATION:\r\n\r\nCandidate should be a college student or recent college graduate; must be available a minimum of 3 days a week and a minimum of 90-day commitment. Flexible schedule to accommodate academic schedules; Candidate selected may arrange academic credit from the appropriate departments. Internship can be tailored to fulfill academic requirements. We will provide referral and letter of recommendation for job placements for excellent interns.\r\n\r\nFilm major preferred but not required. Please consider commute time and your ability to commit to the full term of internship (just like any other important things in life). No long distance commuter will be considered. Please send cover letter and rsum as attachments to: postca@multivisionnaire.com with subject line \"Intern - Film Distribution/Development [specify Summer or Fall]\". Also tell us (a) how will this internship specifically help you; and (b) whats the most important film for you.','FILM DISTRIBUTION INTERNSHIP / SUMMER (JUN 18  SEPT 7, 2018) or FALL (SEPT 17  DEC 19,','','publish','closed','closed','','film-distribution-internshipsummer-jun-18sept-7-2018-or-fall-sept-17dec-19','','','2018-04-17 07:43:24','2018-04-17 07:43:24','',0,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2322',0,'noo_job','',0),(2323,30,'1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','MultiVisionnaire Pictures','MultiVisionnaire Pictures','','publish','closed','closed','','multivisionnaire-pictures','','','1970-01-01 08:00:00','1970-01-01 08:00:00','',0,'',0,'noo_company','',0),(2324,30,'2018-04-11 00:00:00','2018-04-11 00:00:00','<h2>Description</h2>\r\nAs a valuable member of the Ryan Center team, you will assist with a variety of programs and events while learning a variety of marketing essentials. T