f not all rehearsals and performances, running the board during performances and tech, able to rapidly change tasks, take notes at rehearsals and meetings, manage and assist with technical elements of lighting and set during load-in, collaborate with Festivity staff on installing set in space, ensure that all is well before performances and all is struck after each performance. \n<br /> \n<br />SD: Record and edit voiceover text and incorporate found sounds where necessary; incorporate into tech of piece so that it can be controlled from the booth. Remain flexible as to needs. \n<br /> \n<br />Set/Costume/Prod. Designer: Design, source materials, and build assigned portion of production in collaboration with director and playwright. Use MFTA, Goodwill, and other unconventional sources for materials. Ensure ease of use with rest of production and with the space after installation.<h2>Requirements</h2> Stage Manager / Assistant Director: Must have some experience in production, preferably professional; some technical ability; must be able to lift heavy objects and assist with load-in and striking. \n<br /> \n<br />Sound Designer: Must have previously done sound design for live performance; must be able to provide own equipment for recording, editing, and possibly playing sound in space for performance; preferably can provide video examples of work. \n<br /> \n<br />Set/Costume/Production Designer: Must have some background in production design; must be able to work on limited budget (and therefore able to frugally source materials); preferably can provide examples of past work.','Early Summer Internship At Professional Off-Off Broadway Production','','inherit','closed','closed','','2009-autosave-v1','','','2018-04-15 14:54:05','2018-04-15 14:54:05','',2009,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2346',0,'revision','',0),(2347,1,'2018-04-15 16:30:57','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\n    \"old_sidebars_widgets_data\": {\n        \"value\": {\n            \"wp_ina