ner][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Home V5','','inherit','closed','closed','','866-revision-v1','','','2018-04-15 16:36:46','2018-04-15 16:36:46','',866,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2349',0,'revision','',0),(2352,1,'2018-04-16 02:30:10','2018-04-16 02:30:10','<h2>Description</h2>\nThis is an unpaid internship, college credit is available. Must be available at least 3 days a week and a minimum of 4 hours a day.\n\nThe National Association of Latino Independent Producers (NALIP) is seeking motivated, hard-working individuals to join the Digital Production Team. As the premiere non-profit organization working to promote and advocate for Latinos in media, we are constantly producing content to move careers forward. The Digital Production Team oversees all original content produced by NALIP in addition to the development and preparation for the NALIP Media Summit.\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\nCapture BTS footage and still photography of NALIP Productions.\n\nCreate highlight/sizzle reels from archived footage.\n\nBrainstorm and develop various forms of promotional material.\n\nOrganize and maintain multiple hard drives.\n\nResearch upcoming trends and Latino content creators.\n\nResearch potential partnerships/collaborations for the NALIP Media Summit.\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\nBe proficient in DSLR workflows.\n\nBe proficient in Adobe Suite or Creative Cloud  Premiere Pro (Photoshop, Illustrator, After Effects and Final Cut are a plus).\n\nHave working knowledge of codecs, frame rates and delivery formats.\n\nWork well within a team.\n\nBe able to both provide and respond well to constructive criticism.\n\nPay high attention to detail.\n\nHave prior experience managing multiple, simultaneous projects.','Digital Production Internship','','inherit','closed','closed','','1983-autosave-v1','','','2018-04-16 02:30:10','2018-04-16 02:30:10','',1983,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2352',0,'revision','',0),(2353,1,'2018-04-16 02:49:52','2018-04-16 02:49:52','<h2>Description</h2>\nThe purpose of this internship is to provide qualified individuals with essential experience in customer service, facility operations and event management. This is a hybrid position, where the intern(s) will work closely with multiple departments within the organization. These departments include, but are not limited to: Track Operations, Customer Experience, Events and Marketing. The intern(s) will be responsible for assisting in ALL daily operations within the designated department as well as assisting in the planning and implementation of event such as; corporate events, private parties, and rental racing series. The intern(s) will also be responsible for completing a capstone project, which will be presented to the Unser Karting &amp; Events Leadership Team at the end of the program.\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\n Be Actively Engaged and 100% responsible for all training and development  Learn the foundations of each hourly position by working the position:\n\no Customer Experience Advisor\n\no Track Marshal\n\no Mechanic (shadow)\n\no Performance Division o Event Captain\n\n Each Intern will also be responsible for their own Capstone Project. This project requires the student to perform an impactful project to benefit both the organization and the students professional development (i.e., a project worthy of putting on a resume). This project does not have to be adopted by the organization, but it must be completed. The project can be designed to solve an existing issue or an idea that could potentially increase revenue of the facility.\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\nEDUCATION:\n\n Progress towards degree, major in Sports Administration, Sports Management or Hospitality  Minimum junior or senior level or recent graduate (if a recent graduate, must have graduated no longer than 1 year previous to internship semester)  Non-sports administration/sports management or hospitality will be considered for this position.\n\nEXPERIENCE:\n\n Work experienced in the sports or motor sports field, 1+ years (sports facilities, go-karting, or other motor sports environment)  Leadership experience in the sports/motor sports field, 1+ years  Demonstrates a passion and interest for working in a super-high volume, high-fun operations environment\n\nTIME COMMITMENT:\n\n Full-time, 40 hours per week  13-week intern program  Ability to work varied shifts, including mornings, mid-shifts, evenings, weekends and holidays','Summer Internship Unser Karting & Events Centennial','','inherit','closed','closed','','2045-autosave-v1','','','2018-04-16 02:49:52','2018-04-16 02:49:52','',2045,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2353',0,'revision','',0),(2354,1,'2018-04-16 02:50:01','2018-04-16 02:50:01','<h2>Description</h2>\nSeeking eager, self-motivated college students for Social Media Marketing &amp; Event Planning Internship at Spiritual Spectra. If you\'re looking for an internship that is fulfilling - helping others, fun - working in a positive environment, holistic - understanding of mind-body-spirit connection, and educational - learning social media marketing and event planning skills with hands-on experience that you can add to your resume, then you\'ve found it!\n\nAll interns can list Spiritual Spectra as job experience on their resume after their internship. Interns will have the opportunity to job shadow at events and expos and help organize and execute workshops, speaking engagements and events. Successful interns will receive a letter of recommendation either for their next position or scholarship and can list Spiritual Spectra as a reference on their resum. Successful is defined as exceeding not just meeting expectations. Questions? Contact us at info@spiritualspectra.com.\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\nThis is an unpaid internship providing students with experience in Social Media Marketing and Event Planning under the supervision of a former Web Designer and Social Media Marketer. Duties assigned will include updating of Spiritual Spectras social media sites and blog; assistance with marketing efforts including email marketing and distributing marketing materials; event planning and management of workshops, speaking engagements and events; and administrative functions.\n\nHours: Approximately 10-12 hours a week with a flexible schedule (combination of on-site &amp; off-site)\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\nQualifications:\n\n 36 college/university credits with a minimum 3.0 GPA\n\n Experience with Social Media preferred but not required\n\n Some experience organizing events preferred but not required\n\n Experience with Microsoft Office\n\n Strong oral and written communication skills\n\n Strong organizational skills &amp; detail-oriented\n\n Reliable, responsible and self-motivated\n\n Positive attitude &amp; a desire to contribute and learn','Social Media Marketing & Event Planning Intern - Summer 2018 semester','','inherit','closed','closed','','2049-autosave-v1','','','2018-04-16 02:50:01','2018-04-16 02:50:01','',2049,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2354',0,'revision','',0),(2355,1,'2018-04-17 07:41:29','2018-04-17 07:41:29','<h2>Description</h2>\nABOUT MULTIVISIONNAIRE PICTURES\n\n=================================\n\nCompany: MultiVisionnaire Pictures is an established international film distribution and production company known in the global film industry. We are based in east side of Los Angeles, distribute and manage the marketing and financial processes for independent films worldwide. (\n<a href=\"http://www.multivisionnaire.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">www.multivisionnaire.com</a>)\n\nDESCRIPTION:\n\nWe are looking for a resourceful, dynamic self-starter to mentor. Non-paid intern will be mentored in the acquisition, distribution and marketing process of independent films and TV programs; and participate in the preparation of various international film markets (Cannes, American Film Market, etc.). The right candidate will gain invaluable, hands-on experience in the international film business.\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n Assist with preparation for worldwide film markets with the team\n\n Assist with research, analysis and review of independent films\n\n Assist with marketing campaigns, screenings, film releases and film festivals\n\n Assist with international and domestic film distribution and delivery process\n\n Assist with company\'s PR and social media management\n\n Participate in development, research and production process of feature films and TV series\n\n Additional tasks and ad hoc projects to be determined\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\nQUALIFICATIONS :\n\n College major in film, media, marketing, communications, or related field with strong research skills\n\n Passion for films and high literacy in film elements and various genres of independent films\n\n Articulating and charismatic interpersonal communication in writing, in person and on the phone\n\n Personable, professional demeanor, ethical and able to handle confidential matters\n\n Attention to detail (prequalifier: read this listing closely and write a professional cover letter)\n\n Common sense and some basic software skills (Word, Excel, etc.)\n\n One of the following:\n\na) Script writing and reading experience\n\nb) Final Cut Pro editing skill and usage of HD video camera\n\nAPPLICATION:\n\nCandidate should be a college student or recent college graduate; must be available a minimum of 3 days a week and a minimum of 90-day commitment. Flexible schedule to accommodate academic schedules; Candidate selected may arrange academic credit from the appropriate departments. Internship can be tailored to fulfill academic requirements. We will provide referral and letter of recommendation for job placements for excellent interns.\n\nFilm major preferred but not required. Please consider commute time and your ability to commit to the full term of internship (just like any other important things in life). No long distance commuter will be considered. Please send cover letter and rsum as attachments to: postca@multivisionnaire.com with subject line \"Intern - Film Distribution/Development [specify Summer or Fall]\". Also tell us (a) how will this internship specifically help you; and (b) whats the most important film for you.','Media Intern (Film/Video/Photo)','','inherit','closed','closed','','2322-autosave-v1','','','2018-04-17 07:41:29','2018-04-17 07:41:29','',2322,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2355',0,'revision','',0),(2356,1,'2018-04-17 08:02:55','2018-04-17 08:02:55','<h2>Description</h2>\nSpice Boutique is a women\'s clothing store located in Dearborn, MI. We\'ve been in business going on 3 years and we\'re looking to build our team with experienced and eager individuals.\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\n- Create signage, newsletters, email campaigns, online promotions, etc.\n\n- Provide support to social media efforts to target new audiences.\n\n- Assist with trade shows and special events to promote company and increase attendance.\n\n- Research and analyze competitor marketing and sales materials.\n\n- Collaborate on team presentations for management and clients.\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\n- Pursuing a Bachelors Degree in Marketing\n\n- Possess excellent written and verbal communication and customer service skills.\n\n- Possess creativity, flexibility, variety, and growth potential.\n\n- Should be open-minded, a fast learner, enthusiastic, and adaptable.','Marketing Intern','','inherit','closed','closed','','1968-autosave-v1','','','2018-04-17 08:02:55','2018-04-17 08:02:55','',1968,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2356',0,'revision','',0),(2357,1,'2018-04-17 08:03:01','2018-04-17 08:03:01','<h2>Description</h2>\nSpice Boutique is a women\'s clothing store located in Dearborn, MI. We\'ve been in business going on 3 years and we\'re looking to build our team with experienced and eager individuals.\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\n- Assist in all aspects of video and photographic communications and contribute to planning and storyboarding\n\n- Assist in the end-to-end process from storyboarding to logistics to shooting to editing and publishing\n\n- Film video and shoot photographs in studio and field environments\n\n- Record desktop computer screens and actions for demo and training videos\n\n- Use existing original and stock footage to produce new videos\n\n- Contribute to mixing and editing to create polished and engaging videos\n\n- Publish videos primarily to the web and touch-up still photography\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\n- Have the potential to deliver videos and photos that succinctly and clearly tell the desired story\n\n- Ability to deliver videos with cuts, graphics, sound and other elements that convey a quality production value and a level of technical sophistication\n\n- Experience with Final Cut Pro, Adobe Premiere, Adobe Captivate and Adobe Photoshop\n\n- Knowledge of digital videography and photography cameras and equipment','Media Intern (Film/Video/Photo)','','inherit','closed','closed','','1970-autosave-v1','','','2018-04-17 08:03:01','2018-04-17 08:03:01','',1970,'http://ec2-184-73-133-229.compute-1.amazonaws.com/?p=2357',0,'revision','',0),(2358,1,'2018-04-17 08:03:09','2018-04-17 08:03:09','<h2>Description</h2>\nSpice Boutique is a women\'s clothing store located in Dearborn, MI. We\'ve been in business going on 3 years and we\'re looking to build our team with experienced and eager individuals.\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\n- Assists in the design and development of layouts for marketing materials, using appealing graphics that are well organized\n\n- Responsible to incorporate current design trends into each unique layout to produce an up-to-date style for custom ads\n\n- Ability to exercise good judgment when interpreting instructions and to identify the strengths and weaknesses of alternative solutions\n\n- Utilize strong written skills and bring ef